            "subject": "LU-19074 ec: optimize ec_encode_data addressing overhead"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2025-05-31 19:39:06.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2025-05-31 19:51:12.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-19074 ec: add loop unrolling for common source counts",
        "message": "LU-19074 ec: add loop unrolling for common source counts\n\nFurhter optimizations from Claude - significant speedup\nfrom loop unrolling.\n\nAdd specialized loop unrolling optimizations for common erasure\ncoding configurations (4, 6, and 8 data disks) to eliminate\nloop overhead and improve register utilization.\n\nThe optimization unrolls the inner source loop for the most\ncommon EC configurations, hoisting table pointer calculations\nand reducing branch overhead in the critical encoding path.\n\nPerformance improvements from loop unrolling:\n- Small blocks (4KB, 4+2 EC): 1.66x speedup, 121->201 MB/s\n- Medium blocks (64KB, 4+2 EC): 1.66x speedup, 120->199 MB/s\n- Large blocks (1MB, 8+4 EC): 3.09x speedup, 11->34 MB/s\n\nCombined with previous addressing optimizations, this provides\nsubstantial performance improvements for Lustre erasure coding\noperations across common configurations.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I9b2dc63426f2da71dcc85613cd3102f7d5c92c57\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
